<CON:9E>CLS<CON:05>: Clear the Screen<CON:0D>
<CON:0D>
<CON:9A>DESCRIPTION<CON:05><CON:0D>
<CON:0D>
The CLS command clears the screen. This has the same effect as typing PRINT CHR$(147) or typing SHIFT+CLR\HOME.  This command is useful when programs and commands have cluttered up the screen, and is also useful in BASIC programs to PRINTing to an empty screen.
